{
  "texts": [
    "If y ̸ ⊑ f i (x), then y ′ = y ∧ -f i (x) ̸ = ⊥.",
    "Since f i is the left adjoint of ■ i, we have x ⊑ ■ i f i (x) from f i (x) ⊑ f i (x), so x ∧ ♦ i -f i (x) = ⊥, which implies x ∧ ♦ i y ′ = ⊥.",
    "Thus, we do not have xR i y.Another important fact is that for a CV-BAO, its full frame and principal frame are the same.Lemma 5.16 (Full = Principal Frame of a CV-BAO).",
    "For any CV-BAO A, A u = A p.Proof.",
    "As shown in the proof of Fact 4.49, if ⟨A, ≤⟩ is a complete Boolean lattice and ⟨S, ⊑⟩ is the result of deleting the bottom element as in Definition 5.14, then the set RO(S, ⊑) of regular open sets in the downset topology on ⟨S, ⊑⟩ is exactly the set of principal downsets in ⟨S, ⊑⟩ plus ∅, so P u = P p.Theorem 5.17 records the crucial properties of the (•) p and (•) u transformations."
  ]
